The rand fell to a one-year low on Monday amid the fear of a ratings downgrade and concern about President Jacob Zuma's possible plan to push through free higher education. The pound also weakened as Brexit negotiators face a crucial deadline and the future of Prime Minister Theresa May comes into question. The dollar, however, had a good day as tax reform hopes spurred the currency on. Craig Erlam, senior markets analyst from Oanda gives us some insight into where he thinks the rand is headed.